&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Remove all unused&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pacman -Qdtq | sudo pacman -Rs -
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Remove multi-lib packages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pacman -R &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;LANG&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;C pacman -Sl multilib | grep installed | cut -d &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39; &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; -f 2&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Once done edit &lt;code&gt;/etc/pacman.conf&lt;/code&gt; and comment out the ``[multilib]` section&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Re-install all packages (not AUR)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pacman -Qqn | sudo pacman -S -
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Re-install all AUR packages&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Package Management - Debian/Ubuntu</title><link>https://notes.markridgwell.com/posts/linux/package-management-debian/</link><pubDate>Wed, 01 Mar 2023 08:47:11 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://notes.markridgwell.com/posts/linux/package-management-debian/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="package-management---debianubuntu" class=link_owner&gt;
